AB  - IMPORTANCE Dichotomous dermatologic depictions of heroes and villains in movies have been used since the silent film age.
   OBJECTIVE To evaluate the hero-villain skin dichotomy in film by (1) identifying dermatologic findings of the all-time top 10 American film villains, (2) comparing these dermatologic findings to the all-time top 10 American film heroes quantitatively and qualitatively, and (3) analyzing dermatologic portrayals of film villains in depth.
   DESIGN, SETTING, AND PARTICIPANTS In this cross-sectional study, dermatologic findings for film heroes and villains in mainstream media were identified and compared quantitatively using a chi(2) test with a <.05, as well as qualitatively. The all-time top 10 American film villains and heroes were obtained from the American Film Institute 100 Greatest Heroes and Villains List.
